trainData <- sample(1:nrow(model_data_no_na), 0.7*nrow(model_data_no_na))
data.train <- model_data_no_na[trainData,]
data.test <- model_data_no_na[-trainData,]

*Highly correlated:*
Should we remove some of them?
purpose_credit_card <-> purpose_debt_consolidation
purpose_credit_card <-> purpose_home_improvement
purpose_credit_card <-> purpose_other
purpose_debt_consolidation <-> purpose_home_improvement
purpose_debt_consolidation <-> purpose_other

Some of the other purposes are semi-highly correlated (60-70). May be worth a look.

*Note* Gwen confirmed that none of this matters because each loan would only have one purpose.


# Tune the model with the parameters we found by increasing flexibility
Note that this will not find the optimal model. Maybe int_rate ~ poly(revol_util,3) and nothing else is the best model, and this will never test that.

Note: This will take a long time to run. The idea is to run it for each parameter we choose.

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->

```r
```r
cv.error.10=rep(0,10)
for (i in 1:10){
    glm.fit = glm(int_rate ~ poly(revol_util,i) + inq_last_6mths + purpose_credit_card + verification_status_Verified + annual_inc + funded_amnt_inv + purpose_debt_consolidation + `verification_status_Source Verified` + home_ownership_MORTGAGE + revol_bal + dti + initial_list_status_w + pub_rec + delinq_2yrs + purpose_home_improvement + total_pymnt + purpose_major_purchase + total_acc + open_acc + acc_now_delinq + purpose_small_business + purpose_moving + purpose_other + purpose_house + purpose_medical, data = model_data_no_na)
    cv.error.10[i] = cv.glm(model_data_no_na,glm.fit,K=10)$delta[1] # Setting K=10 means 10-fold CV
}
cv.error.10

## Training the model on ridge regression

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxucHJlZGljdG9ycy5UcmFpbiA8LSBtb2RlbC5tYXRyaXgoaW50X3JhdGUgfiAuLCBkYXRhLnRyYWluKVssLTFdICMgcHJlcGFyZSBmb3JtYXQgZm9yIGdsbW5ldFxub3V0cHV0cy5UcmFpbiA8LSBkYXRhLnRyYWluJGludF9yYXRlICAjIHByZXBhcmUgZm9ybWF0IGZvciBnbG1uZXRcbm1fcmlkZ2UuVHJhaW4gPC0gZ2xtbmV0KHByZWRpY3RvcnMuVHJhaW4sIG91dHB1dHMuVHJhaW4sIGFscGhhID0gMCkgIyBkbyB0aGUgZml0XG5cbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r
predictors.Train <- model.matrix(int_rate ~ ., data.train)[,-1] # prepare format for glmnet
outputs.Train <- data.train$int_rate  # prepare format for glmnet
m_ridge.Train <- glmnet(predictors.Train, outputs.Train, alpha = 0) # do the fit


<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->

## Test the ridge regression

We can use the predict() function to make predictions with ridge regression

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxucHJlZGljdG9ycy5UZXN0IDwtIG1vZGVsLm1hdHJpeChpbnRfcmF0ZSB+IC4sIGRhdGEudGVzdClbLC0xXSAjIHByZXBhcmUgZm9ybWF0IGZvciBnbG1uZXRcbnJpZGdlLnByZWQgPC0gcHJlZGljdChtX3JpZGdlLlRyYWluLCBuZXd4ID0gcHJlZGljdG9ycy5UZXN0LCBzID0gYmVzdF9sYW1iZGEpICMgcyBzcGVjaWZpZXMgdGhlIGxhbWJkYSB0byB1c2VcbiMgQ29tcHV0ZSBNU0UganVzdCBmb3IgZnVuIC0gbWF5YmUgdG8gY29tcGFyZSBsYXRlciB3aXRoIG90aGVyIG1vZGVsc1xuKE1TRV9yaWRnZSA8LSBtZWFuKChkYXRhLnRlc3QkaW50X3JhdGUtcmlkZ2UucHJlZCleMikpIFxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
predictors.Test <- model.matrix(int_rate ~ ., data.test)[,-1] # prepare format for glmnet
ridge.pred <- predict(m_ridge.Train, newx = predictors.Test, s = best_lambda) # s specifies the lambda to use
# Compute MSE just for fun - maybe to compare later with other models
(MSE_ridge <- mean((data.test$int_rate-ridge.pred)^2))

## Training the model on LASSO

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxucHJlZGljdG9ycy5MQVNTTy5UcmFpbiA8LSBtb2RlbC5tYXRyaXgoaW50X3JhdGUgfiAuLCBkYXRhLnRyYWluKVssLTFdICMgcHJlcGFyZSBmb3JtYXQgZm9yIGdsbW5ldFxub3V0cHV0cy5MQVNTTy5UcmFpbiA8LSBkYXRhLnRyYWluJGludF9yYXRlICAjIHByZXBhcmUgZm9ybWF0IGZvciBnbG1uZXRcbm1fcmlkZ2UuTEFTU08uVHJhaW4gPC0gZ2xtbmV0KHByZWRpY3RvcnMuTEFTU08uVHJhaW4sIG91dHB1dHMuTEFTU08uVHJhaW4sIGFscGhhID0gMSkgIyBkbyB0aGUgZml0XG5cbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r
predictors.LASSO.Train <- model.matrix(int_rate ~ ., data.train)[,-1] # prepare format for glmnet
outputs.LASSO.Train <- data.train$int_rate  # prepare format for glmnet
m_ridge.LASSO.Train <- glmnet(predictors.LASSO.Train, outputs.LASSO.Train, alpha = 1) # do the fit


<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->

## Test the LASSO regression

We can use the predict() function to make predictions with LASSO regression

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxucHJlZGljdG9ycy5MQVNTTy5UZXN0IDwtIG1vZGVsLm1hdHJpeChpbnRfcmF0ZSB+IC4sIGRhdGEudGVzdClbLC0xXSAjIHByZXBhcmUgZm9ybWF0IGZvciBnbG1uZXRcbkxBU1NPLnByZWQgPC0gcHJlZGljdChtX3JpZGdlLkxBU1NPLlRyYWluLCBuZXd4ID0gcHJlZGljdG9ycy5MQVNTTy5UZXN0LCBzID0gYmVzdF9sYW1iZGFfTEFTU08pICMgcyBzcGVjaWZpZXMgdGhlIGxhbWJkYSB0byB1c2VcbiMgQ29tcHV0ZSBNU0UganVzdCBmb3IgZnVuIC0gbWF5YmUgdG8gY29tcGFyZSBsYXRlciB3aXRoIG90aGVyIG1vZGVsc1xuKE1TRV9yaWRnZSA8LSBtZWFuKChkYXRhLnRlc3QkaW50X3JhdGUtTEFTU08ucHJlZCleMikpIFxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
predictors.LASSO.Test <- model.matrix(int_rate ~ ., data.test)[,-1] # prepare format for glmnet
LASSO.pred <- predict(m_ridge.LASSO.Train, newx = predictors.LASSO.Test, s = best_lambda_LASSO) # s specifies the lambda to use
# Compute MSE just for fun - maybe to compare later with other models
(MSE_ridge <- mean((data.test$int_rate-LASSO.pred)^2))
